title.narrative: Montenegro Institutional Development and Agriculture Strengthening (MIDAS)

description.narrative: The new objectives of the Project are: (i) to improve delivery of government assistance for sustainable agriculture and rural development in a manner consistent with the EU's pre-accession requirements; (ii) to increase the experience of Montenegrin authorities in administering rural development grants in accordance with EU-IPARD core rules, and (iii) to support a selected number of agricultural holdings and food establishments in upgrading towards EU standards.

target.value: Fully compliant monitoring and evaluation system, eligible for EU accreditation.

title.narrative: Feasibility Study on safe disposal of animal by-products prepared and legal framework improved.

baseline.value: National, non-EU compliant system of safe disposal of ABPs in place

target.value: Legal framework on safe disposal of animal by-products drafted.

title.narrative: EU IPARD compatible Rural Development Plan, including agri-environmental measures, submitted to EU.

baseline.value: No EU IPARD compatible Rural Development Unit or Plan.

target.value: Final IPARD Program II submitted to EU

title.narrative: EU IPARD compatible rural development measures fully integrated in MAFWM support programs.

baseline.value: No EU IPARD compatible rural development measures in MAFWM support programs

target.value: Rural development measures defined in EU IPARD program

title.narrative: Number of analysis methods of the Veterinary Diagnostic Laboratory in Podgorica ISO 17025 accredited.

baseline.value: No accreditation at present, overlapping competence in food safety system.

target.value: Achieved. Vet Diagnostic Laboratory in Podgorica has 16 analysis methods ISO17025 accredited

title.narrative: Agricultural Census is implemented and results disseminated.

target.value: Main agricultural census implemented. Statistical register established

title.narrative: Adoption of agri-environmental measures among beneficiaries.

baseline.value: No awareness and use of agri-environmental measures among farmers, processors, and rural communities.

target.value: Farm Register software and hardware system in place, registration of farms initiated and ongoing.

title.narrative: Actions implemented toward Montenegro IPARD accreditation: adoption by Government of the IPARD program; Accreditation package submitted to EU;Paying Agency premises according to EU standards completed

target.value: IPARD program II approved by EU, updated accreditation package according to IPARD program II and submitted for nationalaccreditation, Paying Agency building, IT and Farm Registry system functional.

title.narrative: Marine Biology Institute in Kotor functioning as NRL in adequate facilities.

baseline.value: No suitable facilities in place. No clearly defined role in food safety system, no routine testing performed.

target.value: Full monitoring of sea waters and aquaculture products in line with national legislation.

title.narrative: Veterinary and phyto-sanitary border controls performed in EU-compliant facility in Bar.

target.value: Building completed, equipment procured and installed.

title.narrative: Food establishments classified and annual control plans prepared.

target.value: Procedures for classification of food establishments and annual control plans completed according to EU standards.

title.narrative: All agricultural and rural development investments executed through an EU IPARD compatible Proto-Paying Agency (as approved by the World Bank).
Investments in agricultural and rural development in line with IPARD measures

title.narrative: Critical elements of the food safety system upgraded in EU compliant manner.

baseline.value: Reference Labs lacking equipment and/or facilities, BIPs and food processing establishments not meeting EU standards, animalby-products not safely disposed of

target.value: Lab accreditation completed, supply of BIP equipment, full monitoring of water and aquaculture products, food establishmentsmeeting EU standards for approval
